ProcessMethodMessageEvent
public class ProcessMessageEvent
extends MessageEvent

A ProcessMessageEvent contains information about a message generated from a process usually via a ProcessTrace. Encapsulates message information that can work in a distributed environment.

ProcessMessageEvent

public ProcessMessageEvent(Object source,
                           String processID,
                           int level,
                           String key,
                           Class classKey,
                           Resource resource,
                           String messageLookup,
                           Object[] args)
Creates a ProcessMessageEvent with a source.
Parameters:
level - the "verbosity". Higher is more verbose (less likely to be "listened" for).
processID - a non-null String identifing the process.
key - an arbitrary String key for grouping MessageEvents
classKey - a Class to be associated with this MessageEvent. Allows for a hierarchical grouping of messages. Should normally be the class of the object creating the message.
resource - the Resource used to "translate" the full message text.
messageLookup - the key used to look up the full text in resource
args - the arguments used in a call to MessageFormat.format.
